    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1986-05-23T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1986-05-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="107"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d107">
                <head>107. Memorandum From the President’s Assistant for National Security Affairs
                        (<persName corresp="#p_PJM_1">Poindexter</persName>) to President <persName
                        corresp="#p_RRW_1">Reagan</persName>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d107fn1">Source: National Security Council,
                        National Security Council Institutional Files, Box SR–093, <gloss
                            target="#t_NSDD_1">NSDD</gloss>–227. Secret. Sent for action. Prepared
                        by <persName corresp="#p_LR_2">Linhard</persName> and <persName
                            corresp="#p_KS_1">Kraemer</persName>. <persName corresp="#p_RRW_1"
                            >Reagan</persName> wrote his initials in the upper right-hand corner of
                        the memorandum. A stamped notation at the top of the memorandum reads:
                        “Signed.”</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1986-05-23">May 23, 1986</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>Draft <gloss target="#t_NSDD_1">NSDD</gloss> on Interim Restraint</item>
                </list>
                <p rend="sectiontitleital">Issue</p>
                <p>Should you approve the draft <gloss target="#t_NSDD_1">NSDD</gloss> on <gloss
                        target="#t_US_1">U.S.</gloss> interim restraint policy at <hi rend="italic"
                        >Tab A</hi>?<note n="2" xml:id="d107fn2">Printed as <ref target="#d108"
                            >Document 108</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p rend="sectiontitleital">Background</p>
                <p>The draft <gloss target="#t_NSDD_1">NSDD</gloss> is based upon the draft
                    Presidential statement which we discussed on Wednesday.<note n="3"
                        xml:id="d107fn3">May 21. <persName corresp="#p_RRW_1">Reagan</persName> met
                        with <persName corresp="#p_SGP_1">Shultz</persName> and <persName
                            corresp="#p_PJM_1">Poindexter</persName> in the Oval Office from 1:28
                        until 1:56 p.m. (Reagan Library, President’s Daily Diary) No minutes were
                        found.</note>
                </p>
                <p rend="sectiontitleital">Discussion</p>
                <p>The <gloss target="#t_NSDD_1">NSDD</gloss> differs from the Presidential
                    statement only in that it adds some additional detail to some of the taskings
                    and addresses the issue of encryption which should be kept out of the public
                    record.</p>
                <p rend="sectiontitleital">Recommendation</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">OK NO</hi>
                </p>
                <p>___ ___ That you approve and sign the draft <gloss target="#t_NSDD_1"
                        >NSDD</gloss> at <hi rend="italic">Tab A</hi>.<note n="4" xml:id="d107fn4">
                        <persName corresp="#p_RRW_1">Reagan</persName> initialed his approval and
                        wrote a checkmark next to his initials.</note>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
